{"lemma":"جَرَّةٌ","slug":"جَرَّةٌ","root":"ج.ر.ر","root_slug":"ج-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5386"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jar, amphora, olla","examples":[{"text":"عَثَرْتُ عَلَى جَرَّةٍ ذَهَبًا.","english":"I stumbled upon a jar of gold."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"instance noun of جَرَّ (jarra)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"track, furrow, trail, what is there after one draws (جَرَّ (jarra))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cud, what a ruminant (مُجْتَرّ (mujtarr)) chews"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَرُؤَ (jaruʔa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew גֵּרָה (gerá, “cud”).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5386","headword_ar":"جَرَّةٌ","root":"jr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A jar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well-known vessel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an earthen vessel; a vessel made of potters' clay:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, IDrd, * S, * K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything made of clay:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) dim."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jurayorapN","text_ar":"جُرَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiraArN","text_ar":"جِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~aAtN","text_ar":"جَرَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Msb, K,) [or this last is rather a coll. gen. n., signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pottery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jars,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in relation to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorapN","text_ar":"تَمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, accord. to some, this is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~apN","text_ar":"جَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) Beverage of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"made in such a vessel is forbidden in a trad.: (Mgh, TA:) but accord. to IAth, the trad. means a vessel of this kind glazed within, because the beverage acquires strength, and ferments, more quickly in a glazed earthen vessel. (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jir~apN","text_ar":"جِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A3-  and see what here next follows."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","TA","T","S","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}